// ============================================================================
// 50-eclipse-obd-poweroff.rules
//
// PolicyKit rule granting user 'mcornelison' the
// org.freedesktop.login1.power-off action without interactive auth.
//
// Why: eclipse-obd.service runs as User=mcornelison (unprivileged) and
// the V0.24.1 graceful-shutdown ladder invokes
// `systemctl poweroff` at TRIGGER. Without this rule, the call fails
// with "Interactive authentication required." (I-036, Drain 22
// 2026-05-15 forensic). Latent since V0.24.1 deploy 2026-05-04 --
// every drain hard-crashed at buck-dropout floor.
//
// Scope: power-off only. Reboot/halt/suspend are NOT granted. If
// future stories need reboot rights (e.g. update-applier), add a
// SECOND rule file (51-...) rather than widening this one.
//
// Install: deploy-pi.sh copies this to
//   /etc/polkit-1/rules.d/50-eclipse-obd-poweroff.rules
// (root-owned, 0644). PolicyKit auto-reloads on file change; no
// systemctl daemon-reload needed.
//
// Reference: I-036, US-341 (Sprint 37 V0.27.11), Spool 2026-05-15
//   Drain 22 double-P0 inbox note.
// ============================================================================

polkit.addRule(function(action, subject) {
    if (action.id == "org.freedesktop.login1.power-off" &&
        subject.user == "mcornelison") {
        return polkit.Result.YES;
    }
});
